<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870428-0109 </DOCNO><HL> Grumman Corp. UnitReceives Navy WorkTotaling $32.8 Million</HL><DD> 04/28/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GQ LTV MAS MDDEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Grumman Aerospace Corp., a unit of Grumman Corp., won Navy contracts totaling $32.8 million for A-6F and F-14D aircraft simulators and E-2C aircraft improvements.    AM General, a unit of LTV Corp., received Army contracts totaling $20.5 million for high-mobility multipurpose motor vehicles.    NI Industries Inc., a unit of Masco Corp., was issued Army contracts totaling $14.1 million for cartridge cases for tank ammunition.    McDonnell Douglas Corp. received Navy contracts totaling $13.6 million for FA-18 aircraft improvements. </TEXT></DOC>